                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d936">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.00116 E.W./9–1844: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Minister in Ireland</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Gray</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-09-19T16:00:00-04:00"
                            >September 19, 1944—4 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>179. Reurtel 148, September 18. When we approached other governments on this same
                    subject a few weeks ago we acted alone, though later informing the British and
                    Russians. We understand that the British in some cases at least have supported
                    our request. Ireland was not included in the original list of countries
                    approached. It is our thought here that the same procedure should be followed in
                    the case of Ireland, that is, representations by the United States alone,
                    supported later by the British if the British so desire. Since we <pb
                        facs="1443" n="1429" xml:id="pg_1429"/> wish to make a press statement at
                    once please proceed with request and inform Maffey. We are informing
                        London.<note n="47" xml:id="d936fn47">Telegram 7632, September 19, 4 p.m.,
                        not printed.</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
